Field Detail

MSS

public static final long MSS
The maximum segment size (in bytes): An IP-packet over Ethernet has a payload of up to 1500 bytes. For simplicity, the inner headers (of TCP or UDP) are disregarded.

getErrorProbability

protected double getErrorProbability(long size,
                                     GnpNetLayer sender,
                                     GnpNetLayer receiver)
Calculates the error probability for the transmission of a NetworkMessage. (Maps the error probability of a single packet to the size of the whole NetworkMessage.)

Parameters:
size - The size of the NetworkMessage (in bytes).
Returns:
The error probability.

getLatency

public long getLatency(NetLayer sender,
                       NetLayer receiver)
Calculates the latency for a small NetworkMessage that is send successfully (using TCP or UDP). Bandwidth and size are ignored, because a small NetworkMessage is received instantaniously.

Specified by:
getLatency in interface NetLatencyModel
Parameters:
sender - The NetWrapper that acts as sender.
receiver - The NetWrapper that acts as receiver.
Returns:
The latency (in ZE).
